This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 2014 as National Donate Life Month. The proclamation acknowledges the courageous individuals who make the decision to give the gift of life through organ, eye, and tissue donations. It highlights the importance of organ donation, stating that over 120,000 Americans are currently on the transplant list and 18 die each day waiting for a donation. The proclamation encourages Americans to consider becoming donors and provides information on how to sign up in their state's donor registry. It also mentions the HIV Organ Policy Equity Act, which allows for research on organ donation between individuals with HIV, potentially saving more lives. The proclamation calls upon various groups and organizations to work together to increase the number of organ and tissue donors in the country.